Mentioned him a few days ago again, but my all time favorite religious anecdote is St. John of Shanghai administering last rites to a woman who was dying of rabies, in the final stages of her disease.

After receiving the Eucharist, she was seized by nausea and spasm and ended up violently vomiting the communion out on the floor. So St. John proceeded to consume the vomited substance because it's still the body of Christ with everyone else screaming and begging him not to do it
Nothing bad happened to him afterwards ofc. even though it was soaked in rabies saliva. The Communion cannot transmit any diseases. Put that in your virology textbook and smoke it.
